page.title: 17Landscape
page.content: We came to the gateway by the motorway (B4) and saw ahead of us an arching tunnelway of trees.We saw Chestnuts, Oak,Silver-Birch and Beech trees. A foot path led us through fields of wheat and barley into a small wood.In the field were electricity Pylons .In front of us was the farm house in Maidenbower Farm. All around us were wild flowers-cowparsley,honeysuckle, blue-bells,priwinkle,bird's foot, and wood sorrel.There were buttercups, daisies,thistles, dandelions, clover and nettles. we saw lots of insects too moths, caterpillars,butterflies, ladybirds,horseflies,hover flies and daddy long legs.On our way home we heard a black bird singing in the distance and we saw a robin in a tree. A flock of starlings flew over our head as we got in the mini-bus to go home.
